Activists close to SAPS whistleblower Patricia Mashale say the year she has spent in hiding has taken a serious toll on her health and the financial and emotional wellbeing of her family. She fled the country after receiving zero protection from authorities. For more , eNCA speaks to Professor Mary de Haas from KZN Violence Monitor. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Calls for the protection of whistleblowers always amount to nothing or worse - the targeting of those exposing corruption. READ: SAPS whistleblower Patricia Mashale flees SA That is the concern raised by activists following revelations that SAPS whistleblower Patricia Mashale and her husband fled the country. There are even claims that hitmen were hired from KwaZulu-Natal to kill them. Watch the video above for more details.